<br>
And I agreed with them, I hate click stick clerics that refuse to rez a corpse that's right in front of them when they're doing nothing.  I don't like druids that give the tired old &quot;I'm not a SoW machine&quot; speech.  I play a cleric, my wife a druid, I'm used to getting random tells of,&quot;Can you rez me?&quot; at least every half hour.  It's just mana, I don't mind.  And now that KEI is researchable and I watched someone give it away in Nexus last night chanters have absolutely no cause to charge these exorbitant prices.  It's pure greed.  You guys want to bitch and whine about how much you paid for KEI, start a thread and bitch.  But don't take it out on the populace.<br>
<br>
Most chanters have taken the hint from the populace and have started offering KEI free, or for donation, not the &quot;KEI for 100p donation&quot; BS.  First of all, demanding 100p per cast isn't a donation, it's a fee, see the rant post on CR about that, not started by me.  But hey, anyone that want's to flame me, maybe you should know something.  This is why I posted originally, and man was I pissed.<br>
<br>
I got asked right after a naggy raid to help a rogue that was on the raid set up a Kith raid for his epic.  Me and my wife spent an hour recruiting people from all over to join.  The rogue brought a couple of lvl 60's that offered to help including a 60 enchantress that did nothing but tag along and loot everything she could get her grubby little paws on.  When we got to the camp the rogues designated for the raid, I as the leader of a group full of tanks, asked very politely for KEI from the raid chantress.  I was promptly told &quot;You con green to me, give me 100p and I'll KEI you.&quot;  I figure she must think I'm a wandering person that is just begging KEI, so I explained that I was the group leader for one of the raid groups and had a lot of tanks to keep alive not to mention the MA.  I get a much more curt, &quot;I know, 100p or no KEI&quot;  I asked the rogue who was leading about this and he said he's talk to her about it.  Next thing I know she's gating off with about 150pp in loot and I found out later that my wife, leader of her group, had paid the 100pp per group member, 600pp!!!, because she had it and wasn't about to argue with the greedy chanter.  trust me, had I had more than 20pp to my name I might have thought of that too, but a raid member is obliged to offer buffs to other raid members, and given that there is no component for KEI, thus it costs only mana, there was no cause for a charge to be applicable.  But hey, I'm sure that some of you guys feel this is acceptable.<br>
<br>
Of course hey, if you few posters want to flame me, go for it, but guess what, the message is out, and most chanters have seen the light.  Thank God.  And as far as not taking KEI, I generally don't, if I'm passing through somewhere and see it offered I ask, if not, I play without, I've been playing since before KEI and I do still remember how to manage my mana.  <br>
